-- Pound Rises Versus Euro After Bank of England Pauses Bond Buying
-- B y   L u c y   M e a k i n
-- 2012-11-08T12:04:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-08/pound-rises-versus-euro-after-bank-of-england-pauses-bond-buying.html
The pound strengthened versus the
euro and pared a drop against the dollar after the Bank of
England said it paused its asset-purchase program.  Sterling fell 0.1 percent to $1.5965 as of 12:01 p.m.
London time. It earlier dropped as much as 0.3 percent. It
advanced 0.2 percent to 79.73 pence per euro.  To contact the reporter on this story:
